### `backend/main.py` — FastAPI Application Entry Point

```python
app = FastAPI(title="BridgeDocs API", version="0.1.0")

# CORS: Allows the frontend (localhost:3000) to call the backend (localhost:8000)
app.add_middleware(CORSMiddleware, allow_origins=["http://localhost:3000"], ...)

# Auto-creates all database tables on startup
Base.metadata.create_all(bind=engine)
```

**Key Concept — CORS:** Browsers block requests between different origins (ports count as different). Without CORS middleware, your Next.js frontend on `:3000` would be blocked from calling FastAPI on `:8000`.

