### `frontend/` — Next.js 16 + Tailwind CSS + Shadcn/UI

Created using:
```bash
npx create-next-app@latest ./frontend --typescript --tailwind --app --src-dir
npx shadcn@latest init -d
```

**Why Shadcn/UI?** It's not a component library you install — it copies component source code directly into your project. This means you have full control to customize every button, input, and dialog. Companies like Vercel and Linear use this pattern.

